    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-04-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-04-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="423" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d423">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Uhl</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Muruaga</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-04-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 6,
                                1895</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 17.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: In further reply to your note of the 30th
                            ultimo, stating that you were advised by the consul of Spain at New
                            Orleans that volunteers were being publicly recruited in that city for
                            the purpose of carrying on hostilities in Cuba against the Government of
                            Spain, I have the honor to say that this Department is in receipt of a
                            letter from the Attorney-General, dated to-day, announcing that the
                            United States district attorney at New Orleans has so far failed to
                            discover any basis for the representations contained in your note above
                            referred to. He will, however, continue his investigation of the
                            charge.</p>
                <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Edwin F. Uhl</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
